20240282.review:
Pretty fun game if you like repetitive hacking and mashing.
[olist]
[*] Pull out shield;
[*] intentionally take damage;
[*] mash the sword button during the invincibility period until the robots explode;
[*] repeat.
[/olist]
You run around a dozen or so levels, taking quests for people, which advances the (nonsensical) story and rewards you with new movement abilities. There are also many collectible items that upgrade your abilities. Many of which you can only reach after you get a new movement upgrade. So there is a lot of backtracking.
The boss fights are relatively difficult, but you can always come back when you have leveled up a few times. The armor and health pickups never respawn, but there are plenty around, and the enemies also drop some.

Overall, it's fun if you like running around smashing robots and upgrading your panda. Don't expect amazing level design; the overworld map looks pretty cheap as well, although the music is pretty good.

